        <profileDesc>
            <creation/>
            <abstract>
                <p>A cosmological treatise of a European provenance, possibly translated from a Latin textbook on astronomy by a Jesuit missionary in 
                    Ethiopia in <date>the first half of the 17th century</date> (<bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/WRZ2ALG2"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:HoffmannGeus2020Cosmology"/><title level="a">The Cosmological Treatise in Ms. Paris BnF Éth, Abb. 109: Introduction, Text and Translation with notes</title><title level="j">Rassegna di Studi Etiopici</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Carsten</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Hoffmann</t:surname></author><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Klaus</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Geus</t:surname></author><date>2020</date><biblScope unit="volume">4, 3&lt;sup&gt;a&lt;/sup&gt; Serie (51)</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">61-87</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">62</citedRange></bibl>). The text was believed to be transmitted only in one 
                    manuscript (<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFabb109"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: BNFabb109</span></ref>) employed in all three existing editions, 
                    however, Daria Elagina identified one further witness (<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BLorient816">London, British Library, BL Oriental 816</ref>). A preliminary 
                comparison of the witnesses show some divergencies in readings.</p>
            </abstract>
